Expedition X is an American paranormal reality television series and a spin-off of Expedition Unknown. It features biologist Phil Torres and television host/writer Jessica Chobot and is hosted by Josh Gates, though he does not usually join them in the field, and features topics more explicitly paranormal than those covered in Expedition Unknown.
Expedition X premiered on Discovery Channel on February 12, 2020.
Josh Gates has tapped scientist Phil Torres and paranormal researcher Jessica Chabot to investigate reports of supernatural encounters, mysterious creatures, and astonishing extraterrestrial phenomena. Whether trekking through the remote jungles of Cambodia in search of a legendary ape-man or exploring the secrets of Mexico's infamous Island of the Dolls, the team is searching for answers to the world's most extraordinary mysteries.
Season 8 saw a major change-up in personnel as longtime regular Jessica Chobot left the series, her position eventually being filled by Heather Amaro.
